    <briefdescription>
<para>Command that applies 2D aiming direction to a GameObject. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This command encapsulates an aim request consisting of a normalized direction vector and a frequency factor derived from analog stick magnitude. When executed, it invokes Aim2DComponent::aim() to update the aiming direction and fire frequency.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The target GameObject must have an Aim2DComponent attached for this command to have any effect.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>helios::engine::runtime::messaging::command::Command </para>
</simplesect>
